cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT) for charging and billing in Electric Autonomous Vehicles (EAVs), which involves security and privacy concerns. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the establishment of Machine-to-Machine (M2M) economy, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The proposed architecture and framework involve distributed systems, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed system, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
